  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skin on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add your <strong>dried ancho chilli[es]</strong> to a bowl, cover with <strong>boiled water </strong>and set aside to soak</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649168696447-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649168696447-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649168696447-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649168696447-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1649168696447-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in a bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to the bowl with the garlic and give them a good mix up</p><p>Transfer the <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>coated potatoes</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649168705431-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649168705431-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649168705431-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649168705431-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1649168705431-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the corn until tightly sealed and add to the baking tray[s]</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30-35 min or until the corn is tender and the potatoes are crispy – these are your <strong>smoky corn cobettes </strong>and <strong>mojo de ajo potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649168714035-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649168714035-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649168714035-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649168714035-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1649168714035-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>ancho chilli[es]</strong>,<strong> </strong>then roll up and slice into thin strips (as finely as you can!), discard the seeds and stalk</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> beef stock mix</strong> in 350ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [455ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and add a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>birria-style stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1649168724499-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1649168724499-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1649168724499-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1649168724499-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1649168724499-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced onion</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 4 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>remaining grated garlic</strong>,<strong> remaining ground smoked paprika</strong>, the <strong>sliced ancho chilli </strong>and your <strong>BBQ pulled pork</strong></p><p>Cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1649168733599-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1649168733599-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1649168733599-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1649168733599-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1649168733599-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>birria-style stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15 min or until the pork is warmed through and the sauce has thickened</p><p>Tip: The sauce should be slightly loose so you can dip in your finished tacos!</p><p>Once the pork is warmed through, pull it apart using two forks and mix into the sauce – this is your <strong>birria-style pork</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1649168742967-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1649168742967-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1649168742967-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1649168742967-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1649168742967-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Once everything is nearly ready, add your <strong>tortillas</strong> to a baking tray and put them in the oven for 2-3 min or until they're warmed through (alternatively, add them to a plate and microwave!)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1649168752857-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1649168752857-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1649168752857-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1649168752857-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1649168752857-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, set the <strong>birria-style pork</strong>, <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>tortillas</strong>,<strong> grated cheese</strong>,<strong> remaining sliced onion </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the<strong> chopped coriander</strong> in the centre of the table (build into tacos then dip them back in the birria sauce for an authentic Mexican experience!)</p><p>Serve the <strong>smoky corn cobette[s] </strong>and <strong>mojo de ajo potatoes </strong>to<strong> </strong>the side</p><p>Top<strong> </strong>the corn<strong> </strong>with the<strong> sliced spring onion </strong>and<strong> </strong>the<strong> potatoes </strong>with the<strong> remaining coriander </strong>and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
